they identify Powertech as having the capabilities to undertake and execute its core projects.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\rtlch\af3\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe255\hich\f3\fs22\lang1033\b\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\b {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\i0\b ACTIVITIES OF THE PARTIES}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\rtlch\af3\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe255\hich\f3\fs22\lang1033\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0 [6]\tab  Powertech is involved in the manufacture, supply and design of power electronics and telecommunications sectors products.   In the electronics sector these include among other things; power transformers, lead acid batteries, switches and sockets, high
 voltage machines, accessories for the monitoring metering and protection of electrical power systems, magnetic and electronic lighting control gear, and lighting emergency gear.   In the telecommunications sector, Powertech is active in the design, manufa
cture and supply of infrastructure and products such as: solar systems in the power telecommunications sites, high speed and telecommunications cables, DC power solutions, and accessories for copper and optical fibre infrastructure.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\ql\rtlch\af3\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe255\hich\f3\fs22\lang1033\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0 [7]\tab The other subsidiaries in the Altron Group provide high technology telecommunications, multi-media systems and information technology infrastructure and telecommunications.  Consequently, no overlap or vertical integration occurs in respect of the acti
vities of the subsidiaries of the Altron Group.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\ql\rtlch\af3\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe255\hich\f3\fs22\lang1033\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0 [8]\tab IST Group is active in the electronic and industrial sectors though its five divisions.  IST Data provides telecom operational support solution, geographic information management solutions, and workforce management and mobility solutions.  IST Telecom 
provides voice and data telecommunications technology, and includes products such as battery charging systems and plug power hydrogen fuel cell.  IST Energy provides automation and protection products, systems and solutions, turbine control and turnkey sub
stations for electrical power networks, with General Electric (\'93GE\'94) protection relays, GE supervisory control; GE remote terminal units and GE range of fibre optic products, in the secondary plant segment.   IST Otokon offers energy management and automat
ed meter reading systems and demand-side management solutions, and  IST Industrial  offers  engineering contracting, design and supply of technologically advanced plants for the mining and commercial industries, mainly on water and  air pollution reduction
 and prevention technologies.}
